Description:
Keolis exploite des réseaux de transport public au nom de 300 Autorités Organisatrices dans le monde. Le Groupe est aujourd’hui présent dans 16 pays et sur 4 continents. Leader mondial du métro automatique et du tramway, il est également n°1 du transport sanitaire et n°2 du stationnement en France. Chaque année, 3 milliards de voyageurs utilisent nos services de mobilité partagée.

Keolis Portes et Val de Brie est une jeune entreprise qui exploite le réseau du Pays Briard pour le compte d'Ile-de-France Mobilités. Elle emploie plus de 200 salariés et compte près de 150 véhicules répartis sur 5 centres d'exploitation. 

@PaysBriard_IDFM

Royal Jan de Wit, founded in 1923, the passenger transport specialist.
Royal Jan de Wit joins its businesses in the form of an independent, reliable, flexible, high-quality all-round passenger transport specialist. With a fleet of 100 coaches and 85 minibuses & sedans, we serve all segments of national and international passenger transport.
From exclusive foreign holidays, day trips, school trips, (European) scheduled services, shuttle services and public transport solutions to high-quality 24/7 contract transportation commissioned by companies, institutions and (semi-) public authorities; Royal Jan de Wit always offers tailor-made passenger transport. Our diverse fleet is one of the most differentiated and most modern available. With our fleet and seating capacities from 1 to 92 persons, we can always offer you the perfect transport solution with the right price/quality ratio.

We know what our clients care about: High-quality, modern, comfortable and Sustainable passenger transportation;
Reliability of departure and arrival times;
Skilled and attentive drivers offering a high level of knowledge and service;
Attentive and service-oriented communication.

From the very beginning, our goal has been to offer the best possible service for our clients every day. The Royal Jan de Wit employees guarantee this. The logo of Royal Jan de Wit is the signature of its founder Jan de Wit, in cobalt blue: this signature is synonymous with quality and reliability.

Royal Jan de Wit is one of the few passenger transport companies officially certified with the globally recognised and accredited quality certificate for the specific scope of Passenger Transport, ISO-9001, and the environmental certificate ISO 14001. We also hold the Human Environment and Transport Inspectorate Covenant of the Ministry of Infrastructure and the Environment. Only the best performing people carriers, with regards to organisation and safety in the Netherlands, qualify for this Covenant.

The UK Coach Operators Association was originally the London Tourist Coach Operators Association, which was formed in 1976. Having grown and evolved in recent years, we have adopted a UK-wide role within the coach industry. We pride ourselves in representing Coach Operators who operate coaches anywhere within the UK to anywhere in Europe.

* Business – to and from places of work, training or corporate hospitality;
* Education – Home to School transport; educational visits to places of interest; sport and other inter school events;
* Leisure – travel to sporting events, afternoon or evening entertainment including the Theatre, music concerts and other activities;
*Tourism – day trips to the many sights and experiences that the UK has to offer, leisure breaks, UK wide and international tours;
* Airport Transfers – home to airport or inter-airport journeys;
* Private Hire – available for private events such as birthdays, weddings, school proms and more!

In addition, we can advise members of any requirements for the services they provide to be run under a London Service Permit (LSP) issued by Transport for London (TfL).

Together with our industry partners, we work to improve the infrastructure and environment in the UK for coach travel.

